Module chessclock
Package localization

Class Loc

java.lang.Object
localization.Loc
Direct Known Subclasses:
EmptyLocalization, EnglishLocalization
public abstract class Loc extends Object
An abstract localisation.
The constant fields of this class are used as keys for the data base.
Since:
1.0;

    • retrieveString

      public final String retrieveString(String key)
      Retrieves a string from the localisation data base. If the string cannot be found, the key embraced by pointy crackets is returned instead.
      Parameters:
      key - Key for retrieving the string.
      Returns:
      The string stored or "<key>" if no string has been found.

      1.0;

    • getLanguageCode

      public final String getLanguageCode()
      Returns the language code. This code is in the format of ac-cd. Here, ab is the language and cd refers to a local variant, like french french and belgian french.
      Returns:
      Language code.
      Since:
      1.0;

    • getTimeStrings

      public String[] getTimeStrings(long time)
      Returns string representations displaying the time remaining given in the number of milliseconds, ceiled to the next full deci-second.
      The abstract Loc class provides a default implementation. The return is in the in the format min:sec at index 0, with the seconds being two digits always. At index 1, a string in the format .tens, showing the tens of a second, can be found.
      Subclasses can overwrite this method if they want a different format.
      Parameters:
      time - Time to be represented in milliseconds.
      Returns:
      String representations of the time. First minutes and seconds, second tens of a second.
      Since:
      1.0;
